<subSubSection id="C5DE9CD3FFF02701659BFABD852D969D" pageId="39" pageNumber="340" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="8D7BCF58FFF02701659BFABD849A9541" blockId="39.[151,1437,1326,1605]" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">
<taxonomicName id="4AC4B4DBFFF02701659BFABD80F89565" authority="Ahl, 1931" authorityName="Ahl" authorityYear="1931" box="[151,480,1327,1353]" class="Amphibia" family="Hyperoliidae" genus="Hyperolius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="39" pageNumber="340" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="goetzei">
<emphasis id="BFB0134AFFF02701659BFABD80709564" box="[151,360,1327,1353]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">Hyperolius goetzei</emphasis>
<materialsCitation id="3DACC505FFF027016461FABD80F89565" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3766067308" accessionNumber="ZMB 53181" box="[365,480,1327,1353]" collectionCode="ZMB" country="Tanzania" location="Colour" municipality="Above" pageId="39" pageNumber="340" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Iringa">
<bibRefCitation id="E955B2A9FFF027016461FABD80F89565" author="Ahl" box="[365,480,1327,1353]" firstAuthor="Ahl" pageId="39" pageNumber="340" pagination="1 - 132" refId="ref28575" refString="Ahl, E. (1931) Zur Systematik der afrikanischen Arten der Baumfroschgattung Hyperolius (Amph. Anur.). Mitteilungen aus dem Zoologischen Museum in Berlin, 17, 1 - 132." type="journal article" year="1931">Ahl, 1931</bibRefCitation>
</materialsCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<accessionNumber id="929752BBFFF0270164E6FABD836F9565" box="[490,631,1326,1353]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/protein/ZMB53181" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">ZMB 53181</accessionNumber>
, 
<emphasis id="BFB0134AFFF02701678DFABC83979564" bold="true" box="[641,655,1326,1352]" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">“</emphasis>
Uhehe, Massai-Steppe” (= 
<collectingRegion id="4F0001BAFFF0270166B9FABD82E59566" box="[949,1021,1327,1354]" country="Tanzania" name="Iringa" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">Iringa</collectingRegion>
), 
<collectingCountry id="F5D38FC8FFF02701611CFABD85609565" box="[1040,1144,1327,1353]" name="Tanzania" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">Tanzania</collectingCountry>
. 
<location id="881B9983FFF02701618EFABD85C89565" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:056D7E4EFFF0270E659BFB74829F90FA:881B9983FFF02701618EFABD85C89565" box="[1154,1232,1327,1353]" country="Tanzania" municipality="Above" name="Colour" pageId="39" pageNumber="340" stateProvince="Iringa">Colour</location>
in alcohol: 
<collectingMunicipality id="6D1F5522FFF02701605EFABD84859565" box="[1362,1437,1327,1353]" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">Above</collectingMunicipality>
bright grey-red, with large dark brown marbling on the side of the head and body which has darker margins.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8D7BCF58FFF02701659BFAE580009669" blockId="39.[151,1437,1326,1605]" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">
<taxonomicName id="4AC4B4DBFFF02701659BFAE5836295BD" authority="Schiotz, 1982" authorityName="Schiotz" authorityYear="1982" box="[151,634,1399,1425]" class="Amphibia" family="Hyperoliidae" genus="Hyperolius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="39" pageNumber="340" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="viridiflavus" subSpecies="reesi">
<emphasis id="BFB0134AFFF02701659BFAE580CD95BC" box="[151,469,1399,1425]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">Hyperolius viridiflavus reesi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="E955B2A9FFF0270164D1FAE5836295BD" author="Schiotz" box="[477,634,1399,1425]" firstAuthor="Schiotz" pageId="39" pageNumber="340" pagination="269 - 276" refId="ref34209" refString="Schiotz, A. (1982) Two new Hyperolius (Anura) from Tanzania. Steenstrupia, 8, 269 - 276." type="journal article" year="1982">Schiøtz, 1982</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. ZMUC 
<accessionNumber id="929752BBFFF0270167D1FAE4822195BD" box="[733,825,1398,1425]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/R77205" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">R77205</accessionNumber>
, Magombero Forest, 
<collectingCountry id="F5D38FC8FFF027016124FAE5858895BD" box="[1064,1168,1399,1425]" name="Tanzania" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">Tanzania</collectingCountry>
. The 
<typeStatus id="527F71FAFFF0270161C1FAE585E595BD" box="[1229,1277,1399,1425]" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">type</typeStatus>
was collected close to the localities of the sequenced material, and this form is known to be widely distributed on the central 
<collectingCountry id="F5D38FC8FFF0270165CBFA2D803495F5" box="[199,300,1471,1497]" name="Tanzania" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">Tanzania</collectingCountry>
highlands (
<bibRefCitation id="E955B2A9FFF0270164A0FA2D835295F5" author="Schiotz" box="[428,586,1471,1497]" firstAuthor="Schiotz" pageId="39" pageNumber="340" refId="ref34233" refString="Schiotz, A. (1999) Treefrogs of Africa. Edition Chimaira, Frankfurt am Main, 350 pp." type="book" year="1999">Schiøtz, 1999</bibRefCitation>
). Phase J colour in life: back silvery-brown with a darker pattern of spots and an irregular hourglass pattern. Sides of head and body dark, without a subdermal dark lateral streak. Phase F: Back yellow to light green, flanks with a conspicuous subdermal lateral streak, overlain by 2–3 yellow vertical stripes.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8D7BCF58FFF02701659BF9E1852D969D" blockId="39.[151,1436,1651,2037]" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">
Sequences were available from Kibasira Swamp and Mang’ula, (close to Magombero Forest) 
<collectingCountry id="F5D38FC8FFF0270161B9F9E1840296A1" box="[1205,1306,1651,1677]" name="Tanzania" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">Tanzania</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation id="15FFD3DDFFF027016025F9E1849796A1" box="[1321,1423,1651,1677]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="40.[151,250,1838,1862]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,237,1814]" captionTargetId="figure-63@40.[151,1435,237,1814]" captionTargetPageId="40" captionText="FIGURE 10. Localities of sequences (black circles), type localities (stars) and location of junior synonyms of Hyperolius noblei (A), H. goetzei (B), H. spatzi (C) and H. dintelmanni (D). Locality codes are explained in Table 3." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6538300" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6538300/files/figure.png" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">Fig. 10B</figureCitation>
). The minimum uncorrected 
<emphasis id="BFB0134AFFF0270164C5F90580F8969C" box="[457,480,1687,1712]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">p-</emphasis>
distances from other clades were 4.0–7.0% (
<tableCitation id="C046FAE3FFF0270166DCF905853F969D" box="[976,1063,1687,1713]" captionStart="TABLE 2" captionStartId="20.[151,239,762,788]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="TABLE 2. Uncorrected minimum p-distances as percentages between the clades. GOE—Hyperolius goetzei, NOB—H. noblei, MAR—H. mariae, VIR—H. viridiflavus, GLA— H. glandicolor, MAG—H. marginatus, TUB—H. tuberculosa, BAN—H. bangwae, DIN—H. dintelmanni, MOR—H. marmoratus, NIT—H. nitidulus, SPA—H. spatzi, PAR—H. parallelus." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/D9BB9FD0FFC32732659BFD6880129370" pageId="39" pageNumber="340" tableUuid="D9BB9FD0FFC32732659BFD6880129370">Table 2</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C5DE9CD3FFF0270E65CBF929829F90FA" lastPageId="40" lastPageNumber="341" pageId="39" pageNumber="340" type="description">
<paragraph id="8D7BCF58FFF0270165CBF929842397A5" blockId="39.[151,1436,1651,2037]" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">
<bibRefCitation id="E955B2A9FFF0270165CBF929806D96F9" author="Poynton" box="[199,373,1723,1749]" firstAuthor="Poynton" pageId="39" pageNumber="340" pagination="37 - 41" refId="ref33660" refString="Poynton, J. C. (1977) A new Bufo and associated Amphibia from southern Tanzania. Annals of the Natal Museum, 23, 37 - 41." type="journal article" year="1977">Poynton (1977)</bibRefCitation>
recognised 
<taxonomicName id="4AC4B4DBFFF0270164F0F929838596F9" box="[508,669,1723,1749]" class="Amphibia" family="Hyperoliidae" genus="Hyperolius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="39" pageNumber="340" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="BFB0134AFFF0270164F0F929836F96F9" box="[508,631,1723,1749]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">Hyperolius</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
from central 
<collectingCountry id="F5D38FC8FFF02701663EF929828F96F9" box="[818,919,1723,1749]" name="Tanzania" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">Tanzania</collectingCountry>
with lateral black markings that show through the skin, which 
<bibRefCitation id="E955B2A9FFF027016445F94D80F696D5" author="Schiotz" box="[329,494,1759,1785]" firstAuthor="Schiotz" pageId="39" pageNumber="340" pagination="269 - 276" refId="ref34209" refString="Schiotz, A. (1982) Two new Hyperolius (Anura) from Tanzania. Steenstrupia, 8, 269 - 276." type="journal article" year="1982">Schiøtz (1982)</bibRefCitation>
described as 
<taxonomicName id="4AC4B4DBFFF02701678AF94D83EE96D4" authorityName="Schiotz" authorityYear="1982" box="[646,758,1759,1784]" class="Amphibia" family="Hyperoliidae" genus="Hyperolius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="39" pageNumber="340" phylum="Chordata" rank="variety" species="viridiflavus" variety="reesi">
<emphasis id="BFB0134AFFF02701678AF94D83EE96D4" box="[646,758,1759,1784]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">H. v. reesi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Poynton later (1991) recognised 
<taxonomicName id="4AC4B4DBFFF02701617FF94D843396D4" authorityName="Schiotz" authorityYear="1982" box="[1139,1323,1759,1785]" class="Amphibia" family="Hyperoliidae" genus="Hyperolius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="39" pageNumber="340" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="reesi">
<emphasis id="BFB0134AFFF02701617FF94D843396D4" box="[1139,1323,1759,1785]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">Hyperolius reesi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a good species. The dark lateral band is common in other species, as are yellow transverse stripes in some animals. However, 
<bibRefCitation id="E955B2A9FFF0270165D8F8B58048976D" author="Ahl" box="[212,336,1831,1857]" firstAuthor="Ahl" pageId="39" pageNumber="340" pagination="1 - 132" refId="ref28575" refString="Ahl, E. (1931) Zur Systematik der afrikanischen Arten der Baumfroschgattung Hyperolius (Amph. Anur.). Mitteilungen aus dem Zoologischen Museum in Berlin, 17, 1 - 132." type="journal article" year="1931">Ahl (1931)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName id="4AC4B4DBFFF0270164C7F8B58386976C" authorityName="Ahl" authorityYear="1931" box="[459,670,1831,1857]" class="Amphibia" family="Hyperoliidae" genus="Hyperolius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="39" pageNumber="340" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="goetzei">
<emphasis id="BFB0134AFFF0270164C7F8B58386976C" box="[459,670,1831,1857]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">Hyperolius goetzei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingRegion id="4F0001BAFFF0270167E8F8B5823F976D" box="[740,807,1831,1857]" country="Tanzania" name="Iringa" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">Iringa</collectingRegion>
in central 
<collectingCountry id="F5D38FC8FFF0270166ACF8B58510976D" box="[928,1032,1831,1857]" name="Tanzania" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">Tanzania</collectingCountry>
, which 
<bibRefCitation id="E955B2A9FFF02701616CF8B5841F976D" author="Schiotz" box="[1120,1287,1831,1857]" firstAuthor="Schiotz" pageId="39" pageNumber="340" refId="ref34233" refString="Schiotz, A. (1999) Treefrogs of Africa. Edition Chimaira, Frankfurt am Main, 350 pp." type="book" year="1999">Schiøtz (1999)</bibRefCitation>
illustrated in colour from Dabaga near 
<collectingRegion id="4F0001BAFFF0270164B9F8D980E39749" box="[437,507,1867,1893]" country="Tanzania" name="Iringa" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">Iringa</collectingRegion>
. The back is uniform with mottled sides. This species is known from central 
<collectingCountry id="F5D38FC8FFF02701605CF8D981A197A5" name="Tanzania" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">Tanzania</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="E955B2A9FFF0270165C4F8FD807997A5" author="Schiotz" box="[200,353,1903,1929]" firstAuthor="Schiotz" pageId="39" pageNumber="340" refId="ref34233" refString="Schiotz, A. (1999) Treefrogs of Africa. Edition Chimaira, Frankfurt am Main, 350 pp." type="book" year="1999">Schiøtz 1999</bibRefCitation>
). The localities of the 
<typeStatus id="527F71FAFFF027016756F8FD839297A5" box="[602,650,1903,1929]" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">type</typeStatus>
and taxon regarded as a junior synonym are listed in 
<tableCitation id="C046FAE3FFF0270161EDF8FD842E97A5" box="[1249,1334,1903,1929]" captionStart="TABLE 3" captionStartId="43.[151,239,151,175]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="TABLE 3. Codes, localities and co-ordinates for the types and taxa now regarded as junior synonyms of the Hyperolius species, used in figs. 4–10." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/D9BB9FD0FFFC270D659BFF0580AE90FF" pageId="39" pageNumber="340" tableUuid="D9BB9FD0FFFC270D659BFF0580AE90FF">Table 3</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8D7BCF58FFF0270165CBF801821C97D9" blockId="39.[151,1436,1651,2037]" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">
The most common pattern elements in the descriptions of the 
<typeStatus id="527F71FAFFF02701668CF80182A39781" box="[896,955,1939,1965]" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">types</typeStatus>
included in 
<taxonomicName id="4AC4B4DBFFF027016144F80185A29780" authorityName="Ahl" authorityYear="1931" box="[1096,1210,1939,1964]" class="Amphibia" family="Hyperoliidae" genus="Hyperolius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="39" pageNumber="340" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="goetzei">
<emphasis id="BFB0134AFFF027016144F80185A29780" box="[1096,1210,1939,1964]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">H. goetzei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are dorsal marbling (67%), followed by lateral marbling (33%), small dark spots (33%), or a dark lateral band (33%). The percentages are not additive, as the pattern elements may be shared.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8D7BCF58FFFF270E65CBFF05829F90FA" blockId="40.[151,1436,151,214]" pageId="40" pageNumber="341">
The advertisement call (no voucher) is a series of frequency modulated whistles or clicks with a mean length of 
<geoCoordinate id="E8F0A99FFFFF270E659BFF2981C290F9" box="[151,218,187,213]" degrees="0.04" direction="south" orientation="latitude" pageId="40" pageNumber="341" precision="555" value="-0.04">0.04 s</geoCoordinate>
and an emphasised frequency of 2239 
<location id="881B9983FFFF270E679CFF2983A990F9" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:056D7E4EFFF0270E659BFB74829F90FA:881B9983FFFF270E679CFF2983A990F9" box="[656,689,187,213]" country="Tanzania" latitude="-0.04" name="Hz" pageId="40" pageNumber="341" stateProvince="Iringa">Hz</location>
(
<collectingRegion id="4F0001BAFFFF270E67B3FF29821E90F9" box="[703,774,187,213]" country="Tanzania" name="Iringa" pageId="40" pageNumber="341">Iringa</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F5D38FC8FFFF270E661DFF29826390FA" box="[785,891,187,214]" name="Tanzania" pageId="40" pageNumber="341">Tanzania</collectingCountry>
).
</paragraph>
